      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Mary Bachman is a member of the Antique Comb Collectors Club and editor of their newsletter.  She is also the author of <emph render="italic">Collector's Guide to Hair Combs: Identification and Values</emph> (1998).</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Mary Bachman Antique Comb Collection</emph> consists of 21 combs and hairpins.  Most were made in the United States, but the collection also includes a few from France, England, China, and Indonesia.  Materials include brass, silver, horn, ivory, and celluloid.  Most are hand-made, and date from 1850-1969 although one undated item, from China, may be considerably older.</p><p>Identification numbers and descriptions in the inventory below are taken from supplemental information provided by Glenn Beall (see files).</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
